<DocsPage title="Providers — Model Prism" description="Supported LLM provider types, model discovery, connection management, and the model registry in Open Model Prism.">

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Provider Management</h1>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">A <strong class="text-white/80">provider</strong> is any LLM backend that Open Model Prism can forward requests to. Multiple providers can be connected simultaneously; each tenant selects which providers it has access to.</p>

  <h2 id="supported-provider-types" class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Supported Provider Types</h2>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
    <table class="w-full border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Type</th>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Description</th>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">openai</code></td>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">OpenAI Compatible</td>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Direct API key auth. Covers OpenAI, LitServe, LocalAI, LM Studio, and any OpenAI-compatible endpoint.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">bedrock</code></td>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">AWS Bedrock Native</td>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Converse API, Access Key + Secret, VPC endpoint support, IAM roles (default credential chain), streaming, tool calling</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Bedrock VPC Endpoint Support</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">For private connectivity via AWS PrivateLink, enable "Use custom VPC endpoints" in the provider form. Two separate endpoints are supported: one for the Runtime (Converse API chat/streaming) and one for the Control Plane (model listing). Most users don't need this — the default public AWS endpoints work without configuration.</p>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">The Bedrock adapter supports HTTP proxies via the provider's proxy setting. This is required in corporate networks where VPC endpoints are only reachable through a proxy server. The proxy is applied to both Runtime and Control Plane connections.</p>

