  <h2 id="per-provider-proxy" class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Per-Provider Proxy</h2>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Each provider can optionally route all outbound HTTP requests through an HTTP proxy. This is useful in corporate networks where some providers require a proxy to reach the internet while others are accessible directly or via private endpoints.</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-white/55 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li>Enable the <strong class="text-white/80">Use HTTP Proxy</strong> toggle in the provider form</li>
    <li>Enter the proxy URL (e.g. <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">http://proxy.corp.example:8080</code>)</li>
    <li>The proxy setting is per-provider — different providers can use different proxies, or no proxy at all</li>
    <li>Supports HTTP and HTTPS proxy URLs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Adding a Provider</h2>
  <ol class="list-decimal ml-6 text-white/55 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li>Go to <strong class="text-white/80">Providers</strong> in the sidebar</li>
    <li>Click <strong class="text-white/80">Add Provider</strong></li>
    <li>Enter a name and select the provider type</li>
    <li>Enter the <strong class="text-white/80">Base URL</strong> — do not include <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">/v1</code> or <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">/api/v1</code> (auto-detected)</li>
    <li>Enter the <strong class="text-white/80">API Key</strong> (leave empty for local providers like Ollama)</li>
    <li>Click <strong class="text-white/80">Test Connection</strong> — the connection check probes multiple path variants and logs results</li>
    <li>Click <strong class="text-white/80">Discover Models</strong> to auto-populate the model list</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">URL Detection</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Open Model Prism automatically detects the correct API path by probing:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-white/55 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">&lt;baseUrl&gt;/v1/models</code></li>
    <li><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">&lt;baseUrl&gt;/api/v1/models</code></li>
    <li><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">&lt;baseUrl&gt;/models</code></li>
  </ul>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">The detected path is stored as <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">config.options.apiPath</code> and used for all subsequent requests.</p>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">The setup wizard and provider form both warn if the URL contains a <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">/v1</code> suffix and offer a one-click auto-fix.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">HTTP &rarr; HTTPS Upgrade</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">If a connection test succeeds over HTTP but fails over HTTPS, the form suggests switching to HTTPS. If it succeeds over HTTP only, a warning is shown — the connection works but HTTPS is recommended.</p>

  <h2 id="model-discovery" class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Model Discovery</h2>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">After a successful connection test, click <strong class="text-white/80">Discover Models</strong> (or the provider form triggers it automatically). The discovery process:</p>
  <ol class="list-decimal ml-6 text-white/55 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li>Fetches <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">/v1/models</code> from the provider</li>
    <li>For each model: looks up the local model registry (<code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">modelRegistry.js</code>) for tier, pricing, categories, and benchmark scores</li>
    <li>Falls back to <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">models.dev</code> API (or offline snapshot if <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">OFFLINE=true</code>) for additional enrichment</li>
    <li>Saves results to <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">provider.discoveredModels[]</code></li>
  </ol>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Discovered models can be individually edited in the <strong class="text-white/80">Models</strong> page:</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-white/55 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li>Adjust tier and priority within tier (affects routing order)</li>
    <li>Override input/output pricing (USD per 1M tokens)</li>
    <li>Assign routing categories</li>
    <li>Toggle visibility (<code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">visible=false</code> hides from tenant model lists but remains visible to admins, greyed out)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Editable Context Window & Max Output Tokens</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">The Models page now allows editing <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">contextWindow</code> and <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">maxOutputTokens</code> per model (previously read-only).</p>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-white/55 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li>When manually set, values are protected from refresh override via the <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">manualContext</code> flag (same pattern as <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">manualPricing</code>)</li>
    <li>On model discover/refresh: if <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">manualContext</code> is not set, context values are enriched from the registry</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Auto-Refresh Pricing on Discover</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Provider-specific pricing tables override generic registry pricing during model discovery. Pricing is refreshed on every discover unless the admin set it manually (<code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">manualPricing: true</code>).</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Bulk Visibility Toggle</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-white/55 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">"Show selected" / "Hide selected"</strong> buttons in the Models page bulk action bar</li>
    <li>Hidden models are excluded from tenant routing selectors (classifier, default, baseline, fallback)</li>
    <li>Hidden models still appear in whitelist/blacklist config with a <strong class="text-white/80">"hidden"</strong> badge</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Model Search & Bulk Selection</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-white/55 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li>Search field to filter models by name in the Models page</li>
    <li><strong class="text-white/80">"Select all / Deselect all"</strong> buttons that operate on filtered results</li>
    <li>Shift-click selects/deselects a range of models</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Auto-Suggest</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Each model in the registry has an <strong class="text-white/80">Auto-Suggest</strong> button (wand icon) that fills tier, pricing, and categories from the built-in model registry using fuzzy matching. The matching logic runs three passes:</p>
  <ol class="list-decimal ml-6 text-white/55 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li>Exact ID match</li>
    <li>Registry pattern is a substring of the model ID</li>
    <li>Model ID is a substring of the registry pattern</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Model Registry</h2>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">The local model registry (<code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">server/data/modelRegistry.js</code>) contains metadata for 60+ models. Each model is assigned one of eight cost tiers: <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">micro</code>, <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">minimal</code>, <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">low</code>, <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">medium</code>, <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">advanced</code>, <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">high</code>, <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">ultra</code>, or <code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">critical</code>.</p>
  <pre class="bg-[#0d0d14] border border-white/10 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-white/70 mb-6 font-mono"><code>&#123;
  id:            'claude-opus-4-6',
  family:        'claude',
  vendor:        'Anthropic',
  tier:          'ultra',           // 8 tiers: micro, minimal, low, medium, advanced, high, ultra, critical
  inputPer1M:    5.00,    // USD
  outputPer1M:   25.00,   // USD
  contextWindow: 1000000,
  categories:    ['reasoning_formal', 'code_generation', 'system_design'],
  patterns:      ['opus46', 'opus-4-6', 'claude-opus-4-6'],
  benchmarks: &#123;
    intelligence: 93,
    coding:       89,
    math:         88,
    speed:        25,    // 0=slow, 100=fast
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-2">Benchmark Scores</h3>
  <p class="text-white/55 leading-relaxed mb-4">Benchmark scores (0-100 scale) are sourced from public benchmarks (ArtificialAnalysis, LMArena, HumanEval, MATH-500) and used by the routing engine to select the most capable model for a given task type.</p>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
    <table class="w-full border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Axis</th>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Source benchmarks</th>
          <th class="bg-white/5 text-left text-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-sm">Used for routing categories</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">intelligence</code></td>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">MMLU, GPQA, LMSYS Arena</td>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">General reasoning, research, document understanding</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">coding</code></td>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">HumanEval, SWE-bench</td>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm">Code generation, debugging, security review</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="border-t border-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-white/50 text-sm"><code class="bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-[#38bdf8] text-sm font-mono">math</code></td>
